========,1,preface.
Orestes is a town in Monroe Township, Madison County, Indiana, United States.
It is part of the Anderson, Indiana Metropolitan Statistical Area.
The population was 414 at the 2010 census.
========,2,History.
Orestes was founded in 1876 when the railroad was extended to that point.
It may be named after Orestes in Greek mythology.
Orestes was incorporated as a town in 1894.
